<div id="optionsMakeAGraph" class="powerSearchReportPopup">
<p class="smallFont" align="right"><a href="javascript:UnTip();">close</a></p>
<h3>Make a Graph</h3>
<p>
To prepare a graph showing leading items and share data, press the icon at the top of any data field in the spreadsheet or the icon in any field in the blue side bar.  Query Result Filters (yellow side bar) appears any time you concentrate on a single data field. Use these filters to eliminate keywords or remove common terms or consolidate terms. Be sure to check the box to the left of filters you wish to use and then press Apply Selected Filters.
</p>
</div>

<div id="optionsAddAField" class="powerSearchReportPopup">
<p class="smallFont" align="right"><a href="javascript:UnTip();">close</a></p>
<h3>Add a Field</h3>
<p>
To add a data field to your spreadsheet, press Add Field and check any box and then press Submit Query.
</p>
</div>

<div id="optionsAutoFilter" class="powerSearchReportPopup">
<p class="smallFont" align="right"><a href="javascript:UnTip();">close</a></p>
<h3>Drill Down</h3>
<p>
To filter your data, click any word in the spreadsheet.
</p>
</div>

<div id="optionsTypeInFilter" class="powerSearchReportPopup">
<p class="smallFont" align="right"><a href="javascript:UnTip();">close</a></p>
<h3>Type in Filter</h3>
<p>
To further filter any data field, press the data field in the blue side bar to see options. Be sure to check any box you want in your results or deselect those you do not need.  Press Submit Query and results will appear in your spreadsheet.
</p>
</div>

<div id="optionsRunReport" class="powerSearchReportPopup">
<p class="smallFont" align="right"><a href="javascript:UnTip();">close</a></p>
<h3>Run Report</h3>
<p>
To run any of seven reports, press any of the options under Report Selection in the green side bar to the left.
</p>
</div>